claims:
8. A method for installing a thermal management system, the method comprising:
positioning the anisotropic composite against an exterior wall, in which the anisotropic composite consists of alternating layers of insulation and a thermally conductive material;
running a thermal loop along an edge of the anisotropic composite, such that the thermal loop is thermally coupled to the thermally conductive material;
circulating a cooling fluid through the thermal loop, the cooling fluid having a dynamically controlled or floating temperature that is at least a predetermined amount less than an outdoor ambient temperature; and
positioning an outer cladding over the anisotropic composite, wherein the anisotropic composite has an in-plane thermal conductivity that is greater than a through-plane thermal conductivity to reduce heat transfer through the exterior wall.
